Description: Fix 64-bit portability issues
 Three categories of problems fixed:
 .
 1. ppdepack.c: undefined behaviour when shifting uint8_t values into the
    sign bit of a 32-bit int (expressions like data[n]<<24 or 1<<data[n]).
    All byte values are now explicitly cast to ULONG before shifting.
    The size_t argument passed to ppcrack() is also explicitly cast to ULONG
    to document the intentional truncation (Amiga files are always < 4 GiB).
 .
 2. mmcmp.c: the four MMCMP structs are mapped directly onto file data via
    pointer casts. Several fields sit at unaligned offsets (e.g. MMCMPHEADER
    at offset 10), which causes a bus error on strict-alignment architectures
    (arm64, armhf, riscv64). All four structs now carry __attribute__((packed))
    so the compiler generates safe byte-by-byte accesses.
    The size_t-to-uint32_t narrowing in decrunch_mmcmp() is made explicit.
 .
 3. unsqsh.c: two unaligned accesses via raw pointer casts:
    - the SQSH chunk checksum word was read as *(UWORD*)c — replaced by memcpy.
    - xchecksum() received a (ULONG*) pointer to potentially unaligned data;
      the function now takes a byte pointer and uses memcpy to read each word.
